<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10099868>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–12. Specimens of Cicinnoscelis Holland, 1893; Megalosphecia Le Cerf, 1916 and Alonina Walker, 1856: (1) Cicinnoscelis longipes Holland, 1893, ♂, Congo, Eala. (2–3) C. flavipes new sp., ♀, holotype. (4–5) C. krooni new sp., ♀, holotype. (6) Megalosphecia callosoma Hampson, 1919 ♀, holotype. 7–12. Alonina rygchiiformis Walker, 1856, (7) ♂ holotype; (8) ♂, syntype of A. difformis Hampson, 1919 new syn.; (9) ♀, syntype of A. difformis Hampson, 1919 new syn.; (10–11) ♂, Kenya, Eastern Province, road Meru to Nyambeni Hills, 10 km N/E Meru; (12) ♀ South Africa [unknown locality]. Scale bars 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10099868/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10099891>
    dc:description "FIGURES 99–106. Scanning electron microscope pictures of antennae: (99) Cicinnoscelis flavipes new sp., #f holotype; (100) Alonina rygchiiformis Walker, 1856; (101) Anaudia felderi Wallengren, 1863; (102) Austrosetia semirufa Felder & Felder, 1874; (103) Felderiola karooensis new sp.; (104) Monopetalotaxis doleriformis (Walker, 1856); (105) Hagnogyna bartschi (Freina, 2011); (106) Sesia bembeciformis (Hübner, 1803)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10099891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10099893>
    dc:description "FIGURES 107–108. Genitalia of Cicinnoscelis Holland, 1893: (107) Cicinnoscelis longipes Holland, 1893; (108) C. flavipes new sp, holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10099893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

